lity\t500-1,250 hours (CFI-directed instructing)\t500-1,250 hours (CFI-directed instructing)\tDelta Propel requirements (ATP minimum 1,500 after) Time to Endeavor Air Hiring\t18-24 months training + 8-12 months CFI = 26-36 months total\t30 months degree + 12-18 months CFI = 42-48 months total\tSkyborne accelerated path; Liberty standard model Delta Propel Interview\t✅ Guaranteed interview (official academy status)\t⚠️ Conditional interview (must qualify as AABI grad + CFI)\tDelta Propel CFI path requirements Conditional Job Offer (CJO) to Endeavor\t✅ Upon CFI + Delta interview success\t⚠️ Upon CFI + Delta interview success (same odds, but conditional vs. guaranteed)\tDelta Propel program structure Instructor Quality (Mixed Reviews)\t⚠️ Mixed (Yelp 3.5/5; Reddit 50/50 split; some complaints about management)\t✅ Established (AABI-accredited; Academy of Aviation is known regional operator)\tYelp/Reddit reviews; AABI accreditation status Training Environment\tVero Beach (isolated, warm weather year-round)\tWhite Plains/Westchester (NYC Class B airspace, high commercial traffic)\tLocation assessment Guarantee of Completion\t⚠️ No explicit guarantee; program can dismiss students\t⚠️ Standard college standards apply (can be dismissed)\tStandard industry practice Total Cost to Delta Pilot (Endeavor SIC)\t$63K-84K training + living (18 months) = ~$95K-120K\t$110K-150K training + living (4 years) = ~$180K-220K\tFull cost analysis DELTA PROPEL ELIGIBILITY: BOTH PATHWAYS Skyborne Path: Earn Private, Instrument, Commercial, CFI at Skyborne (210 hours) Hired as CFI by Skyborne (guaranteed) Build 500-1,250 hours as CFI instructor Apply to Delta Propel (eligible at 500+ hrs CFI, within 12 months of ATP minimum) Interview with Delta (official academy pathway) Result: Conditional Job Offer (CJO) to Endeavor Air if selected White Plains Path (Liberty + Academy): Earn B.S. degree in Aeronautics from Liberty (4 years) Earn Private, Instrument, Commercial, CFI at Academy of Aviation Hired as CFI by Academy of Aviation (not guaranteed but likely) Build 500-1,250 hours as CFI instructor Apply to Delta Propel (eligible at 500+ hrs CFI; Liberty is AABI-accredited) Interview with Delta (one of 29 AABI schools eligible) Result: Conditional Job Offer (CJO) to Endeavor Air if selected CRITICAL DIFFERENCE: GUARANTEE vs. CONDITIONAL Program Phase\tSkyborne\tLiberty + Academy Official Delta academy?\t✅ YES (designated partner)\t❌ NO (one of 29 AABI schools) CFI employment upon graduation?\t✅ YES (guaranteed hire by Skyborne)\t⚠️ Likely (Academy typically hires grads, but not contractual guarantee) Delta Propel interview guaranteed?\t✅ YES (official academy priority)\t⚠️ YES (AABI eligibility), but competitive screening Conditional Job Offer (CJO) odds?\t~70-80% (official status helps)\t~50-70% (competitive with other AABI schools) TIMELINE COMPARISON Skyborne → Endeavor Air: 18 months: Flight training (P, I, C, CFI) 8-12 months: CFI building hours at Skyborne Apply → Interview → CJO Total: 26-36 months to Endeavor hire White Plains → Endeavor Air: 48 months: B.S. degree + flight training (P, I, C, CFI) via Liberty + Academy 12-18 months: CFI building hours at Academy Apply → Interview → CJO Total: 60-66 months to Endeavor hire Speed Advantage: Skyborne wins by 24-30 months (~2 years faster) COST ANALYSIS Skyborne Total Out-of-Pocket (to Endeavor hire): Flight training: $63K-84K (after $20K Delta aid) Living expenses (18 mo): $18-24K Total: $81K-108K ✅ LOWER COST White Plains Total Out-of-Pocket (to Endeavor hire): Tuition (4 years): $90K-140K Flight training (included in tuition): $50K-70K Living (48 months, est. $1,300/mo): $62K Total: $202K-272K ❌ SIGNIFICANTLY HIGHER FINAL VERDICT: PILOT TRAINING + DELTA PROPEL ONLY Winner\tCategory\tData SKYBORNE\tSpeed to Delta\t26-36 months vs. 60-66 months (2-year advantage) SKYBORNE\tTotal Cost\t$81K-108K vs. $202K-272K ($100K+ savings) SKYBORNE\tCFI Employment Certainty\tGuaranteed hire vs. likely but not guaranteed SKYBORNE\tDelta Propel Priority\tOfficial academy vs. one of 29 eligible schools WHITE PLAINS\tTraining Quality\tAABI-accredited degree vs. standalone certs (credential advantage) WHITE PLAINS\tInstructor Stability\tEstablished regional operator vs. mixed reviews RECOMMENDATION: FOR DELTA PROPEL FOCUSED PILOT ONLY Choose Skyborne if: Speed is critical (get to Endeavor 2 years sooner) You want to minimize cost"}]},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"text":"[Content truncated — view full chat at source URL]"}]},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"text":"Source: "},{"type":"link","href":"https://www.genspark.ai/agents?id=5a71f3aa-f48a-46b9-aeab-525ce2ed9e8f","children":[{"text":"https://www.genspark.ai/agents?id=5a71f3aa-f48a-46b9-aeab-525ce2ed9e8f"}]}]}]
